# Copy to .env.local (Next.js loads it for dev). Do not commit .env.local.
#
# Browser → API base URL (baked at `next build` in Docker).
# - Local dev: match api-express (default dev port 5000), e.g. http://localhost:5000
# - If api-express uses BACKEND_PORT=5001 → http://localhost:5001
# - Host hitting published API only: http://localhost:3001
# - Docker Compose + repo nginx: leave EMPTY so the browser uses same-origin `/api/*`
#   (nginx routes /api/ to api-express). Example: NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5000
#
# Optional: absolute URL to Bull Board when enabled on the API (e.g. http://localhost:5000/admin/queues).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_BULL_BOARD_URL=http://localhost:5000/admin/queues
#
# Optional: client-side max range check for Khanan date-range scrape (should match backend SCRAPE_MAX_RANGE_DAYS)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SCRAPE_MAX_RANGE_DAYS=31
#
# Cookie session mode (Phase B — enabled by default; no flag needed on the frontend).
# Sessions rely on httpOnly cookies (spybot_access, spybot_refresh) set by Express on /api/auth/login
# and /api/auth/generate-token.  The SPA detects an active session by reading the readable
# spybot_csrf cookie (not httpOnly) via hasSpybotSession() / getSpybotToken().
# All fetch calls automatically include credentials: 'include' and X-CSRF-Token via AppShell.
# For local dev against a separate API origin, ensure CORS_ORIGIN_ALLOWLIST on the backend
# includes this Next dev origin (e.g. http://localhost:3000).
#
# Backend auth: production default is cookie-only JWT (no `Authorization: Bearer`). See
# AUTH_ALLOW_BEARER in apps/api-express/.env.example and apps/api-nest/.env.example.
